# 1️. Basic Find Usage

## Find file by name

```bash
find / -name passwd
find /etc -name shadow
find /etc -name passwd
```

---

## Find Dockerfile anywhere in system

```bash
find / -name Dockerfile
```

---

# 2️. Find by File Size

## Files greater than 1GB

```bash
find / -size +1G
```

## Save result to file

```bash
find / -size +1G > /tmp/searchResult.txt
```

## Files smaller than 1KB

```bash
find / -size -1k
```

## Count small files

```bash
find / -size -1k | wc -l
```

---

# 3️. Find by Permission

## Files with 777 permission

```bash
find / -perm 777
```

## Files with 000 permission

```bash
find / -perm 000
```

## Files with 700 permission in /etc

```bash
find /etc -perm 700
```

---

# 4️. Find by User Ownership

## Create user

```bash
useradd rupesh
```

## Find files owned by user

```bash
find / -user rupesh
```

---

# 5️. Using -exec Option

## Create backup directory

```bash
mkdir /tmp/backup-rupesh
```

## Copy all files owned by rupesh to backup directory

```bash
find / -user rupesh -exec cp -rvf {} /tmp/backup-rupesh/ \;
```

---

# 6️. Verify Backup

```bash
ls /tmp/backup-rupesh/
ls -la /tmp/backup-rupesh/
```

---

# Important Find Options

| Option | Meaning |
|--------|----------|
| -name | Search by file name |
| -size | Search by file size |
| -perm | Search by permission |
| -user | Search by owner |
| -exec | Execute command on result |
| {} | Represents found file |
| \; | Ends exec command |

---

#  Tip

If permission denied errors appear, use:

```bash
find / -name passwd 2>/dev/null
```

This suppresses error output.

---

#  Summary

In this practical we:

✔ Searched files by name  
✔ Searched by size  
✔ Searched by permission  
✔ Searched by ownership  
✔ Used -exec for automation  
✔ Redirected output to file  

---

Linux Find command is powerful for:
- System auditing
- Security checks
- Backup automation
- DevOps troubleshooting
